1677cca18","tid":476023,"uid":19557,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-21T15:49:28.000Z","msg":"fbi 終於唔駛捉老翻<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8084ba07cecef37e34b8b40a2e76a2e4d39f7c9d","tid":476023,"uid":35870,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-21T15:52:48.000Z","msg":"FBI<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\nFBI<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\nFBI<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d77083067c0aed519017f654764eddd6e43fc569","tid":476023,"uid":2054,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-21T15:54:02.000Z","msg":"fbi捉你 死撚梗"},{"pid":"7c100e52acc1a530b9e10c2ede5ce91f289b54bc","tid":476023,"uid":79563,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-21T15:55:45.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">FBI</span> <img src=\"/assets/faces/big/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1f90fd421feaf83074ddb1b13299d46fe9af1d27","tid":476023,"uid":5195,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-21T17:02:56.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-12th-us-china-forum-registration-38855283198\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eventbrite.com%2Fe%2Fthe-12th-us-china-forum-registration-38855283198&d=oh0x7qK8nOqAef1Cr4y0b6WGW%2FHqnCni%2B1xW1zXhD2s%3D&h=c657a0c0\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-12th-us-china-forum-registration-38855283198</a><br />\n<br />\nThe 12th US-China Forum will be held on Monday, November 20th at the National Press Club.<br />\n<br />\nThe forum, held alternatively in Hong Kong and Washington since 2012, aims to improve the understanding of North American policymakers of Sino-US relations and to seek constructive ways for the U.S. and China to work together to advance economic development in Asia.<br />\n<br />\nThis year&rsquo;s forum, held in the aftermath of President Trump&rsquo;s visit to China, will assess the current status of US-China relations and will seek ways to broaden the relations beyond the obvious thorny issues of North Korea, South China Sea and trade. To this end we will explore areas of cooperation such as energy security, technological innovation, infrastructure development and the Belt and Road Initiative. A delegation of senior experts from China will travel to Washington to take part in the event.<br />\n<br />\nIAGS is a Washington based think tank dedicated to research and public debate on issues related to energy and security. It is also the parent organization of the United States Energy Security Council, America&rsquo;s highest level extra-governmental energy policy advisory committee. CEFC is a Hong Kong based think tank with special consultative status in the United Nations. It is dedicated to work related to public diplomacy and addressing issues pertaining to the emerging status of China.<br />\n<br />\nFor more information including agenda, please visit: <a href=\"http://oborforum.org\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Foborforum.org&d=oh0x7qK8nOqAef1Cr4y0b6WGW%2FHqnCni%2B1xW1zXhD2s%3D&h=e9203d8f\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://oborforum.org</a><br />\nThere is no fee to attend but registration is by invitation only. Invitations are not transferable and are associated with the email address to which they are sent. To request additional invitations, please email info@iags.org.<br />\nWe hope you are able to join us on November 20th.<br />\n<br />\nLOCATION<br />\n<br />\nThe National Press Club<br />\n529 14th Street NW<br />\n13th Floor<br />\nWashington, DC 20045<br />\nUnited States"},{"pid":"b8c7108880dfaa7a43e9256b1e3a917d882ba316","tid":476023,"uid":5195,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-11-22T05:24:04.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/ass